#  proof_that_0_fact_equals_1
$0! := \Gamma (1)$

$\Gamma (z) := \int_{0}^{\infty} t^{z-1}e^{-t}dt $

$\Gamma (1) = \int_{0}^{\infty} t^{0}e^{-t}dt$

$= \int_{0}^{\infty} e^{-t}dt$

using the substitution method for integration.

$x := -t$

$\implies \frac{dx}{d t} = -1$

$\implies dx = -dt$

And the bounds of the integral are now $0$ to $-\infty$.

$\implies \int_{0}^{\infty} e^{-t}dt = - \int_{0}^{-\infty} e^{x}dx$

We know that the integral of $e^{x}$ is itself, $e^{x}$.

$=-\left[ e^{x} \right] _{0}^{-\infty}$

$ = - (0 - 1) = - (-1) = 1$. QED.

